    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear that feeling of being a ghost behind your own eyes, and it sounds like you're in a very lonely, hollow place right now. It's a heavy weight to carry when you feel disconnected from your own life, like you're just watching a movie of someone else's existence instead of living it.\n\nBut even in that foggy, empty theater, I hope you know that a little bit of you is still there, just hiding out in the shadows. Sometimes, when the world feels too loud or too quiet, we all need a little break, a moment to step back and let the dust settle.\n\nYou don't have to force yourself to feel anything right now. Just breathe, and if you want, you can talk to me about what's making you feel like a ghost. I'm here to listen, and I promise I won't let you feel completely alone.",
